# Commit Policy

Source of truth: @ai/rules/common/commit-message-and-crosslinks.md

## Format

`type(scope): short description` (max 72 chars, imperative, no period)

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `style`, `ci`, `build`, `revert`

Examples:
- `feat(transactions): add filter by category`
- `fix(dashboard): correct kopeck division on balance`
- `chore(deps): upgrade expo-router to 3.5`

## Rules

- No `Co-authored-by:` trailers
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit: generated artifacts, secrets, `.env` files
- Never `git add -A` or `git add .` — stage specific files
- Run `rtk yarn lint` before commit; never commit failing lint
